23/06/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Anticorruption Directorate will launch an investigation against Youth Minister Monica Iacob Ridzi, for suspected embezzlement and misappropriation of state funds, media reported on Monday (June 22nd).
The National Liberal Party filed the case, claiming she abused her position and embezzled funds intended for use in celebrating Youth Day on May 2nd.
The party also asked for Ridzi's resignation.
(Mediafax, Ziare, Realitatea TV - 22/06/09)
